    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Determines when the battery state changes</para>
<para>The BatteryStateService API lets you know when the battery state changes, that is, its current charge level, whether it is plugged and charging. It uses the <ref refid="struct_battery_charge_state" kindref="compound">BatteryChargeState</ref> structure to describe the current power state of Pebble.</para>
<para>Refer to the <ulink url="https://github.com/pebble-examples/classio-battery-connection">classio-battery-connection</ulink> example, which demonstrates using the battery state service in a watchface. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
